help:  (i) tried to determine the specific wells in which each individual=20
plaintiff had an interest; (ii) located, from Rhodes' study, the 2-page=20
sheets for each of those wells; (iii) added up all the over- and undertake=20
"values" (dollar amounts) shown for that well in the Rhodes study; and (iv)=20
applied plaintiffs' percentage interest to that amount.  He then added up th=
e=20
individual well amounts for each plaintiff, to arrive at that plaintiff's=20
